{
  "texts": [
    "1, 2025 the contribution lies in its exploratory approach to the attitudes and perceptions of special education teachers of English as a Foreign Language (EFL) towards the use of ChatGPT as a learning tool.",
    "By employing a mixed-methods approach, the study not only quantifies attitudes, perceived effectiveness, barriers, and future willingness to use ChatGPT but also adds a qualitative dimension through follow-up interviews.",
    "The findings provide valuable insights for the implementation and development of ChatGPT in language teaching for special education students, highlighting the importance of considering inclusive gender approaches and overcoming practical challenges to enhance the effectiveness of this tool in educational contexts.The research developed by Watrianthos et al. [25] provides a comprehensive overview of the emerging landscape of research on the integration of ChatGPT in education.",
    "Through a bibliometric analysis, the study maps publication trends, identifies influential works, and reveals key themes such as applications in higher education, pedagogical strategies, ethical risks, and implications for assessment.",
    "It highlights the rapid growth of publications since the launch of ChatGPT, uncovers significant research gaps, especially in K-12 education, and offers guidance for future research and practical implementation."
  ]
}